      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of recent articles about West Nile virus, which used incorrect New York City Health Department data; 62 confirmed cases of illness in 1999 included 7 deaths from encephalitis</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Tuesday about the discovery of West Nile virus in dead birds on Staten Island and several other articles since March 10 used an incorrect New York City Health Department breakdown of the figures for illnesses caused by the virus in the New York region last year. The 62 confirmed cases in 1999 included 7 deaths from encephalitis, an inflammation of the brain, and 55 other cases of serious illness, according to the federal Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. The 62 cases of illness were not in addition to the deaths.</p>
      </block>
